cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SY 

This paper is about using reinforcement learning to perform robot manipulation tasks without the need for a ground truth state estimator. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also discusses learning policies directly from high-dimensional sensor inputs, which falls under the category of machine learning. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely category. The paper also proposes a reward function for goal-conditioned reinforcement learning, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses using RGB-D images for rope manipulation, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper discusses the convergence of the proposed method, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY).
